name: Radha Krishna Indian Folk Art Styles

metadata.name: Radha Krishna in Odisha Patta Chitra Style
metadata.description: Pattachitra is a traditional painting of Odisha, India. These paintings are based on Hindu mythology. Pattachitra style of painting is one of the oldest and most popular art forms of Odisha. Here Radha Krishna illustrations are done from anatomy stage to complete illustration. The collector will get UHD file of this Art to see the detail on the art.
